  "prompt": "What do if I forget my user id and password of forex card HDFC?",
  "response": "If you forget your user ID or password for your HDFC Forex card, here are the steps you can take to recover them:\n\n1. **Visit the HDFC Bank Forex Card Login Page:**\n   - Go to the official HDFC Bank website and navigate to the Forex card login page.\n\n2. **Forgot User ID:**\n   - Look for the option that says \"Forgot User ID\" or similar.\n   - You may be prompted to provide some information, such as your card number, registered mobile number, and email address.\n   - Follow the instructions provided to retrieve your user ID.\n\n3. **Forgot Password:**\n   - Click on the \"Forgot Password\" link.\n   - You will be asked to enter your User ID, card number, and other details.\n   - Follow the instructions to reset your password. You may receive a temporary password or a link to set a new password via email or SMS.\n\n4. **Contact Customer Support:**\n   - If you are unable to retrieve your user ID or reset your password through the online options, you can contact HDFC Bank customer support.\n   - You can call the HDFC Bank customer care number dedicated to Forex cards or visit the nearest HDFC Bank branch for assistance.\n   - Ensure you have your Forex card and identification documents handy when contacting support.\n\n5. **Email Support:**\n   - You can also send an email to HDFC Bank\u2019s customer service explaining your issue.\n   - Provide necessary details like your name, card number, and registered mobile number.\n\nAlways ensure you follow the security protocols and provide accurate information to facilitate the recovery process smoothly.",
